.TH "fsverity_hash_buffer" 9 "fsverity_hash_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsverity_hash_buffer \- hash some data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsverity_hash_buffer
.BI "(struct fsverity_hash_alg *alg "  ","
.BI "const void *data "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "u8 *out "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "alg" 12
the hash algorithm to use
.IP "data" 12
the data to hash
.IP "size" 12
size of data to hash, in bytes
.IP "out" 12
output digest, size 'alg->digest_size' bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Hash some data which is located in physically contiguous memory (i.e. memory
allocated by \fBkmalloc\fP, not by \fBvmalloc\fP).  No salt is used.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
